title: Thonburi United F.C.
text:
Thonburi United Football Club (<a href="Thai%20alphabet">Thai</a> สโมสรฟุตบอลธนบุรี ยูไนเต็ด), is a Thai <a href="Association%20football">football</a> club under the stewardship of <a href="Thonburi%20University">Thonburi University</a> based in <a href="Bangkok">Bangkok</a>, <a href="Thailand">Thailand</a>. The club is currently playing in the <a href="Thai%20League%203">Thai League 3</a> Bangkok metropolitan region.
History.
In 2016, the club has established and competed in <a href="Thailand%20Amateur%20League">Thailand Amateur League</a> Bangkok Metropolitan region, used <a href="Thonburi%20University%20Stadium">Thonburi University Stadium</a> as ground. They competed in the amateur league to 2017 and 2018 season continuously.
In 2019, the club has promoted to <a href="Thai%20League%204">Thai League 4</a> or also known as Omsin League. The club made the new history by advanced to the round of 16 in <a href="Thai%20League%20Cup">Thai League Cup</a>, they beat Samut Prakan City from Thai League 1 in the round of 32, before defeated to PT Prachuap in the round of 16. The club could advanced to <a href="2019%20Thai%20League%204%20Champions%20League">2019 Thai League 4 Champions League</a>.
